# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TheManual.tech · Environment Variables
# Copy to .env.local for dev. In production (Railway), set via dashboard.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase connection
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.example

# Note: use the legacy eyJ-format JWT anon key, NOT the new sb_ format
# (per FreedomBLiNGs stack learning — the supabase-js client expects legacy JWT)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Admin Tier 4 — The Nucleus (Five Keyholders)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated UUIDs of Bees with Keyholder access to /nucleus.
# Per HONEYCOMB governance canon (§31 Three Switches & Five Keyholders),
# up to 5 entries. Read SERVER-SIDE ONLY by the check-keyholder Edge
# Function — never exposed to the client. Set this in Supabase Edge
# Function secrets, NOT as a VITE_ var.
KEYHOLDER_BEE_IDS=
